FBIS4-56851 "drlat090_m_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-090 Daily Report 6 May 1994 Brazil President Congratulates Leaders on PLO Accord President Congratulates Leaders on PLO Accord PY0905121394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2228 GMT 6 May 94 PY0905121394 Madrid EFE Spanish BFN [Text] Brasilia, 6 May (EFE) -- Today, Brazilian President Itamar Franco sent congratulatory messages to Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat following the recent agreement to establish a Palestine Self-Government Authority [Autoridad Palestina de Auto-Gobierno]. The decision to create a provisional Palestine Self-Government Authority with jurisdiction on the Palestine territories in the Gaza Strip and Jericho is considered "historic" by the Brazilian chief of state. Franco points out that the agreement represents a new horizon for the consolidation of peace, safety, and stability in the Middle East that will benefit the region and all of humanity. Egyptian President Husni Mubarak, who hosted the Rabin-Arafat meeting held in Cairo on 4 May, also received a congratulatory message from Franco.
